        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(tls): add subjectAltName to auto-generated gateway self-signed certificate (fixes #96910)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96910.\n\nWhen gateway TLS is enabled with `autoGenerate=true`, the self-signed certificate had no `subjectAltName` extension. Node.js ≥17 ignores the CN for hostname/IP verification per RFC 6125, causing CLI probe failures.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- New certs: Added `-addext subjectAltName=...` to the openssl command\n- Existing certs: Auto-detect CN-only certs (`CN=openclaw-gateway`, no SAN) and regenerate with SANs\n- Transactional upgrade: old files renamed to `.bak`, restored on failure\n- Custom certs (non-OpenClaw CN) are never touched\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** 10/10 passed\n- New certs verified via `openssl x509 -ext subjectAltName`\n- Custom cert regression: `CN=custom-server` cert loaded unchanged\n- Transactional safety: backup/restore verified\n\n- [x] AI-assisted",
